name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On May 25, China National Radio Military posted a message "What gift do you want to receive this summer?" and attached a picture of an aircraft carrier poster. It hinted at "military reunification of Taiwan" this summer.
This Weibo post sparked heated discussions among netizens. In the comments section of the relevant discussion, netizens said, "I want fairness and justice, free medical care for all, and I want to live on without being oppressed."
As of now, China National Radio Military has deleted the Weibo post.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On May 30, the West Kowloon Court in Hong Kong ruled that 14 people, including Leung Kwok-hung and Wong Pik-wan, were found guilty of "conspiracy to subvert state power", while Lau Wai-chung and Lee Yu-sin were found not guilty.
This is the first time that a defendant in a case under China's "Hong Kong National Security Law" has been found not guilty. The Department of Justice immediately expressed its intention to appeal, and the judge allowed the two to be released on bail under the original conditions. Previously, the conviction rate of the National Security Law was 100%.
